RATLING

Ratlings are rodent-like humanoids known for their exceptional quickness,
high intelligence, and nimble fingers.  They thrive in the ruins of pre-Rifts
cities, making excellent thieves, scouts, and technical experts.  Though
physically unremarkable in strength, their PP and Spd make them hard to hit
and quick to act.

ATTRIBUTES (approximate ranges):
  IQ: 5-20   ME: 4-14   MA: 3-18   PS: 5-20
  PP: 7-22   PE: 3-18   PB: 3-8    Spd: 9-24

DAMAGE POOL:
  SDC: 2d6 x10 (approx 20-120)

SPECIAL ABILITIES:
  - Excellent PP and Spd; fast and precise
  - Above-average IQ; good for technical and rogue OCCs
  - Nimble fingers; natural aptitude for thievery and technical skills

PENALTIES:
  - Below average PB
  - Low physical strength compared to combat-focused races
  - Distrusted in many communities

OCC ELIGIBLE: Yes.
ALIGNMENT: Any.

